<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-03-17T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-03-17T11:00:00-05:00" n="438" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">411.12/1767: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hawks</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-03-17T10:00:00-06:00">March 17, 1934—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>28. Referring to Department’s telegram No. 35, March 16, noon, as a
                            result of further conference with Foreign Office officials, changes on
                            page 8 would read as follows: lines 10 and 11<note n="56" xml:id="d438fn56"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_433">p. 433</ref>, par. (<hi rend="italic">d</hi>), 1. 5.</note>
                            “evidence, with the Brief and Reply Brief, as rebuts evidence, filed
                            with the Answer and Brief, et cetera”. Line 19<note n="57" xml:id="d438fn57"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_433">p. 433</ref>, par. (<hi rend="italic">d</hi>), 1.12.</note>
                            would read: “evidence filed with the Answer or Brief, the additional
                            evidence”.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hawks</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>